reviewText:
I want to tell I am the huge admirer of the Hitman series. There was a pro of Hitman: Codename 47/. A tremendous step in before a plot - Road Movie.


At the best moments of Absolution forces the player to feel like the real murderer improvisator capable to tear off purpose life in one thousand various ways. To strangle the security guard and to change clothes in a new form. Having pulled a cap over the person, to slip by his vigilant colleagues. Having quickly studied a situation round the victim, to make the decision and instantly to carry out it, and then to be dissolved before people around manage to understand something.

Unfortunately, Absolution ‚Äî it also the imposed linear pieces where it is necessary to move forward obediently in the unique way. These are conventions in a stealth which force the project to look bad in comparison with the predecessors. On each plus here easily there is minus. However work of IO Interactive is contrary to mathematical laws, remaining on a positive side of balance.

Advantages:

the best missions offer a choice in a corporate style of Hitman;
intense, dynamic stealth;
high potential for repeated passings.

Shortcomings:

set of boring linear episodes;
sluggish multiplayer;
not ideal system of masking


It is dissatisfied music already unwritten Jesper Kyd to which I listened throughout all last parts.

My assessment = 7\5 Excellent stealth of 2012.
